720073f-a.title: Manhattan: Grand Street - Wooster Street
720073f-a.text:
69-59 Grand Street, south side, at, adjoining, and west of the

724816f-a.title: Manhattan: Wooster Street - Grand Street
724816f-a.text:
Wooster Street, south from Grand Street to its southern end at Canal
Street. Wooster Street is the third of a group of seven streets
laid out parallel to and west of Broadway.
The building in the background is the new New York Telephone Building.
June 23, 1933.
L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
